{"TopicId":215220,"ForumId":208,"TopicTitle":"The sun disappears at certain zoom level in map view","CreatedByName":"last-stop-till-titan","CreatedById":227909,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-16T23:54:27Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"last-stop-till-titan","CreatedById":227909,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-16T23:54:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP Version: 0.1.1.0.21572\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOperating System and version: Windows 11\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCPU and GPU models, any other system\u00A0information which could be relevant: RTX 3070, i9-12900k\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDescription of the bug.:\u00A0Sun goes dark when you zoom into Gilly, Duna, Laythe, etc. (I didn\u0027t try all planets, sun seems to be fine when viewing Kerbin, Eve, and Moho for example)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExpected Behavior: Sun should continue shining (fingers crossed)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSteps to Replicate: Go to Gilly/Duna/Laythe/etc in the tracking station and zoom in\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA list of ALL mods: None\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOther Notes / Screenshots / Log Files (if possible..):\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/Nz3u3EK\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/Nz3u3EK\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-16T00:32:29Z\u0022 title=\u002207/16/2023 12:32  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jul 16\u0022\u003EJuly 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EUpdated the title to The Aziz because it describes the issue better\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-15T22:46:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.3.1 |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Win10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7-10700K | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0RTX2060 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis was happening since 0.1.0 I believe.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAdditional thing, that the sun sphere isn\u0027t rendered in flight view until very close, that looks bad.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EVideo Evidence:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003Cvideo class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 controls=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.global.core.embeddedvideo\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022926\u0022 data-unique=\u0022ydlkqie8r\u0022\u003E\n\u003Csource type=\u0022video/mp4\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_10/son.mp4.e11911ddedff34d32ea18258484981ab.mp4\u0022\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022mp4\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022926\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/attachment.php?id=926\u0026amp;key=dd435a36c9945b54453e184c930fe240\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Eson.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/video\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=son.mp4\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5B6LUQrN77P3ZNiFO3wx6r6JbbaW1TE651cW58jUSdSEGK33GI0j3fcd/U/cAG1nMtwgvoKXafuu/UZ3bX%5D%5B5cfd936ece60e9d1c2b0cc64%5D%5B5cae6868d5198e3703f3a606ff6e5fd1%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan id=\u0022cke_bm_402E\u0022 style=\u0022display: none;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-16T00:33:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/150811-the-aziz/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150811\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@The Aziz\u003C/a\u003E Merged yours with this one. (I brought it out of the archive)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224302990\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215220\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689461207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.3.1 |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Win10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7-10700K | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0RTX2060 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey. Was that 0.1.3.1 or 0.1.3.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-16T07:35:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure on which version it was recorded as it was a few days back, but since .2 was only a hotfix, I assume it still persists.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mushylog","CreatedById":227298,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-25T11:24:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI experience this very frequently, the sun (or Kerbol ) disappears before the silhouette of the planet in focus even overlaps its light. It looks like a mask was applied around each planet, to hide the sun\u0027s light source, but for Gilly/Duna/Laythe and Minmus it seems that this \u0022mask\u0022 is too big, so the sun is hidden when it should not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dandoesstuff","CreatedById":223454,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-27T06:42:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4.1 |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 3200g | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0GTX 1050 ti | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16gb\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMight be fixed, didn\u0027t test in 0.1.5.0, but kerbol turns black when you zoom in the map view\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cvideo class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 controls=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.global.core.embeddedvideo\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022934\u0022 data-unique=\u0022vczyi8rbu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Csource type=\u0022video/mp4\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_10/KerbalSpaceProgram22023_10.15-12_59_53_07.mp4.0b67d33c25c789c54603d0a498d97e7a.mp4\u0022\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/attachment.php?id=934\u0026amp;key=b52acc382925ff7c323a1076961439c4\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022934\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022mp4\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKerbalSpaceProgram22023_10.15-12_59_53_07.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/video\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-27T11:58:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/223454-dandoesstuff/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022223454\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/223454-dandoesstuff/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dandoesstuff\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0merged your report with this one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-10-27T12:09:22Z\u0022 title=\u002210/27/2023 12:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Oct 27\u0022\u003EOctober 27, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-28T08:13:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDefinitely still on 0.1.5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-29T03:26:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Phenom(tm) II X6 1055T Processor 2.80 GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDIA GeForce RTX 2070 SUPER | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E24.0 GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile I was orbiting Kerbin today, I noticed that the Sun was turning black and disappearing, along with some of the planets\u0027 orbit lines, when I zoomed in close to my ship in map view.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Far away, the sun and orbits are all there:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022LmPhPxb.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/LmPhPxb.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. This is the distance at which the sun first turned black. Jool\u0027s, and I think Eeloo\u0027s orbit lines have disappeared:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022mAKWaiC.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/mAKWaiC.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Even closer in, all the planets\u0027 orbit lines are gone:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022HwBF8l8.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/HwBF8l8.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-30T00:41:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/227909-last-stop-till-titan/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022227909\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/227909-last-stop-till-titan/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@last-stop-till-titan\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0moved this report out of the archive\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/150330-cubinator/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150330\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/150330-cubinator/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@cubinator\u003C/a\u003E merged your report\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-07T02:21:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Win 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Ryzen 5 5600x | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A03070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDepending on the zoom level the player-camera is around Minmus (at least) the sun goes out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFar zoom:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022lYNlH2P.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022166.67\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/lYNlH2P.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNext zoom in:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022NlzhgJS.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022166.67\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/NlzhgJS.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00